The paper discusses side-channel attacks on mobile devices, which are a security and privacy concern. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes a new categorization system for side-channel attacks, which involves analyzing and developing countermeasures, indicating that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper discusses the impact of side-channel attacks on mobile devices, which are complex systems, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the sensitive information stored on smartphones, indicating that it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and future research directions in the field, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
